  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to register a startup company for \"Startup India\" campaign and how much will it benefit a startup?",
  "response": "The \"Startup India\" campaign is an initiative by the Government of India to foster and promote entrepreneurship by providing support to startups. The procedure to register a startup under this campaign involves several steps:\n\n### Procedure to Register a Startup for \"Startup India\":\n1. **Incorporate Your Business**:\n   - First, incorporate your business as a Private Limited Company, a Partnership firm, or a Limited Liability Partnership (LLP). This involves registering the business with the Ministry of Corporate Affairs and obtaining the necessary certifications.\n\n2. **Register on the Startup India Portal**:\n   - Visit the Startup India website (startupindia.gov.in) and register your startup by creating a profile.\n   - Fill in the details about your startup, including basic information, details of directors/partners, and other relevant information.\n\n3. **Get DPIIT Recognition**:\n   - After registration, apply for recognition as a \"Startup\" by the Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT).\n   - Log in to the Startup India portal and click on \u2018Get Recognized\u2019 under the \u2018Recognition\u2019 tab.\n   - Fill out the application form by providing the required information and uploading necessary documents:\n     - Incorporation/registration certificate.\n     - Director details.\n     - Proof of concept such as a pitch deck, website link, video, etc.\n     - A brief description of the innovative nature of the business.\n\n4. **Submit the Application**:\n   - Once all the details and documents are provided, submit the application for DPIIT recognition.\n   - The DPIIT will review the application and the startup will be granted recognition if it meets the eligibility criteria.\n\n### Benefits of Registering Under \"Startup India\":\n1. **Tax Benefits**:\n   - Recognized startups can avail tax benefits including a 3-year tax holiday in the first 10 years of incorporation.\n   - Exemption from capital gains tax and investments above fair market value.\n\n2. **Funding Support**:\n   - Access to government schemes and funds such as the Fund of Funds for Startups (FFS).\n\n3. **Ease of Compliance**:\n   - Simplified compliance procedures, self-certification under labor and environmental laws.\n\n4. **Intellectual Property Rights**:\n   - Fast-tracking of patent applications and reduced costs for intellectual property filings.\n\n5. **Networking and Mentorship**:\n   - Access to high-quality mentorship and networking opportunities through various government-organized events and seminars.\n\n6. **Incubation and Accelerators**:\n   - Support for incubation and acceleration through recognized incubators and accelerators.\n\n7. **Government Tenders**:\n   - Easier access to government procurement and tenders.\n\n8. **Credit Guarantee**:\n   - Credit guarantee schemes to help startups secure loans from banks and other financial institutions.\n\nBy registering under the \"Startup India\" campaign, startups can benefit from various government initiatives aimed at easing the process of starting and running a business, fostering innovation, and providing financial support which can significantly contribute to the growth and success of the startup.",
